HEADWORD: Spectrometry
<hw>Spec*trom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Art or process of using a spectrometer, of any
type; -- when used alone, it usually refers to the use of a spectrometer
using light in the visible, infrared, or ultraviolet region.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Spec`tro*met"ric</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>mass spectrometry</b></col>, <cd>the art or process of
using a mass spectrometer to analyse chemical samples.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spectrophone</ent>⟦br⟧
